      "writtenOn": "2017-12-20T05:03:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh my. Do we really need to spin up a thread to do this? Surely we can catch the signal and resume after dlsym() on a single thread.\n\n1. The thread is heavyweight and kind of dirty.\n\n2. It breaks dlerror().\n\nThe typical solution involves a siglongjmp() from the signal handler.",
