      "writtenOn": "2017-12-20T05:03:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Speaking of dlerror(), can we set it ourselves if we catch a signal? Bionic uses a TLS slot to point to the thread’s dlerror() string, TLS_SLOT_DLERROR. It’s a little bit of poking to write our own message there, but if we’re replacing dlsym(), we should replace it fully and properly.",
      "revId": "7072285c6f9bdc244d006958ae6d73569ced1449",
